3^x + x = 85
x\ge 0,3^x\le 85,x\le 4
x<4,3^x<81\implies 3^x+x<85
x
4
x<0,3^x<1\implies -3^x>-1\implies x=85+(-3^x)>84
x<0
a b^x + x = c
a b^x = c-x
 b^x = \frac{c-x}{a}
 e^{x\ln{b}} = \frac{c-x}{a}
 1= \frac{c-x}{a} e^{-x\ln{b}}
  e^{c\ln{b}}= \frac{c-x}{a} e^{-x\ln{b}} e^{c\ln{b}}
  ae^{c\ln{b}}= (c-x) e^{(c-x)\ln{b}}
  \ln{b}.a.e^{c\ln{b}}= \ln{b}(c-x) e^{(c-x)\ln{b}}
  b^c\ln{b}.a= \ln{b}(c-x) e^{(c-x)\ln{b}}
u=\ln{b}(c-x)
 ue^u= b^c\ln{b}.a
u=\ln{b}(c-x)=W(b^c\ln{b}.a)
x=c-\frac{W(a b^c\ln{b})}{\ln{b}}
a b^x + x = c
3^x + x = 85
x=85-\frac{W(3^{85}\ln{85})}{\ln{85}}
